<promed@promedmail.org>
[OIE's Commission for Foot and Mouth Disease and Other Epizootics
evaluated documentation concerning the eradication of FMD submitted
by the delegate of the Republic of Korea and, in accordance with
Resolution No. XVII ("Restoration of recognition of the foot and
mouth disease status of Member Countries") adopted by the OIE
International Committee during its 65th General Session (May 1997),
recognized on 19 Sep 2001 that this country regained its previously
recognised FMD-free status without vaccination. Obviously, this
regained status may be lost now. It will be important, in global
terms, to obtain information on the serotype and subtype of the
current FMD virus isolate and its possible origin. The previous
outbreak was caused by the Pan-Asian O FMDV type, which spread over
vast parts of Asia and to several European countries. Its evolution
during the years 2000-2001, as reported by FAO's European Commission
for FMD (EUFMD), can be seen at:
<http://www.fao.org/livestock/!agah/eufmd/reports/rg2001im/App01.pdf> - Mod.AS
